      • createPropertyPatch

        public static Set<Property> createPropertyPatch(@NonNull
                                                @NonNull String propertyName,
                                                @NonNull
                                                @NonNull Object propertyValue,
                                                String componentName)
        Create a key-value property patch for both read-only and read-write properties.
        Parameters:
        propertyName - The property name, as defined in the DTDL interface.
        propertyValue - The property value, in the format defined in the DTDL interface.
        componentName - (optional) The name of the component in which the property is defined. Can be null for property defined under the root interface.
        Returns:
        The property path for read-only and read-write property updates. The property patch is created in the below format: { "sampleComponentName": { "__t": "c", "samplePropertyName"": 20 } }

      • createPropertyEmbeddedValuePatch

        public static Set<Property> createPropertyEmbeddedValuePatch(@NonNull
                                                             @NonNull String propertyName,
                                                             @NonNull
                                                             @NonNull Object propertyValue,
                                                             @NonNull
                                                             @NonNull Integer ackCode,
                                                             @NonNull
                                                             @NonNull Long ackVersion,
                                                             String ackDescription)
        Create a key-embedded value property patch for read-write properties. Embedded value property updates are sent from a device in response to a service-initiated read-write property update.
        Parameters:
        propertyName - The property name, as defined in the DTDL interface.
        propertyValue - The property value, in the format defined in the DTDL interface.
        ackCode - The acknowledgment code from the device, for the embedded value property update.
        ackVersion - The version no. of the service-initiated read-write property update.
        ackDescription - (optional) The description from the device, accompanying the embedded value property update.
        Returns:
        The property patch for embedded value property updates for read-write properties. The property patch is created in the below format: { "samplePropertyName": { "value": 20, "ac": 200, "av": 5, "ad": "The update was successful." } }

      • createPropertyEmbeddedValuePatch

        public static Set<Property> createPropertyEmbeddedValuePatch(@NonNull
                                                             @NonNull String propertyName,
                                                             @NonNull
                                                             @NonNull Object propertyValue,
                                                             String componentName,
                                                             @NonNull
                                                             @NonNull Integer ackCode,
                                                             @NonNull
                                                             @NonNull Long ackVersion,
                                                             String ackDescription)
        Create a key-embedded value property patch for read-write properties. Embedded value property updates are sent from a device in response to a service-initiated read-write property update.
        Parameters:
        propertyName - The property name, as defined in the DTDL interface.
        propertyValue - The property value, in the format defined in the DTDL interface.
        componentName - (optional) The name of the component in which the property is defined. Can be null for property defined under the root interface.
        ackCode - The acknowledgment code from the device, for the embedded value property update.
        ackVersion - The version no. of the service-initiated read-write property update.
        ackDescription - (optional) The description from the device, accompanying the embedded value property update.
        Returns:
        The property patch for embedded value property updates for read-write properties. The property patch is created in the below format: { "sampleComponentName": { "__t": "c", "samplePropertyName": { "value": 20, "ac": 200, "av": 5, "ad": "The update was successful." } } }
